The National Driving Schools Association of South Africa in Gauteng protested on Wednesday. It wants to shut down 38 Drivers and Learners Testing Centres in the province. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Members of the National Driving Schools Association of South Africa in Gauteng intensified their protest on Friday. Members plan to close all 38 Drivers and Learner Testing Centres in the province. READ: KZN driving schools get a boost On Thursday, they shut down the Sandton licensing department in Marlboro. The association is unhappy with the online booking system for driver’s licences. Watch the video above for more information